{% comment %}
  Gift Guide — quick-view popup (rendered ONCE by the lookbook section and reused
  by every "+" marker). It is an empty shell: assets/gift-popup.js fills the
  title, price, description, and variants from live product JSON each time it
  opens. Built from scratch; markup is dialog-accessible (role, aria, labelled close).

  Static labels here are translation-ready; product content is injected by JS.
{% endcomment %}

<div class="gift-popup" data-gift-popup hidden>
  {%- comment -%} Dimmer; clicking it closes the popup (handled in JS). {%- endcomment -%}
  <div class="gift-popup__overlay" data-gift-popup-overlay></div>

  <div
    class="gift-popup__dialog"
    role="dialog"
    aria-modal="true"
    aria-labelledby="gift-popup-title"
    data-gift-popup-dialog
  >
    <button type="button" class="gift-popup__close" data-gift-popup-close aria-label="Close quick view">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false">
        <path d="M6 6l12 12M18 6L6 18" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="square" />
      </svg>
    </button>

    {%- comment -%} Header: square thumbnail (left) + title / price / description. {%- endcomment -%}
    <div class="gift-popup__head">
      <div class="gift-popup__media">
        <img class="gift-popup__image" data-gift-popup-image src="" alt="" width="123" height="142" />
      </div>
      <div class="gift-popup__info">
        <h2 class="gift-popup__title" id="gift-popup-title" data-gift-popup-title></h2>
        <div class="gift-popup__body">
          <p class="gift-popup__price" data-gift-popup-price></p>
          <div class="gift-popup__description" data-gift-popup-description></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    {%- comment -%}
      Color — built from scratch per Figma "Component 208–210", placed directly
      below the header. A "Color" label, a segmented track of options (each cell:
      a left colour-swatch bar + the value name), and a single black layer that
      SLIDES to the chosen cell while that cell's label inverts to white. The
      options and the slide state (--color-count / --color-i) are filled by JS
      from the product's "Color" option values; the control drives the shared
      controller state, so it sits outside <form> by design (buttons, not inputs).
    {%- endcomment -%}
    <div class="gift-popup__options">
      <div class="gift-popup__color" data-gift-popup-colors hidden>
        <span class="gift-popup__color-label">Color</span>
        <div class="gift-popup__color-options" data-gift-popup-swatches role="radiogroup" aria-label="Color"></div>
        <span class="gift-popup__color-indicator" data-gift-popup-color-indicator aria-hidden="true"></span>
      </div>

      {%- comment -%}
        Size: a custom listbox (Figma Component 212/213) — a trigger styled like
        the select, with an options panel that drops directly below it. JS fills
        the <ul> and manages open/selection so we fully control the dropdown
        (chevron, click-away, styling) without the native picker's limits.
      {%- endcomment -%}
      <div class="gift-popup__option" data-gift-popup-sizes hidden>
        <span class="gift-popup__option-label" id="gift-popup-size-label">Size</span>
        <div class="gift-popup__select-wrap" data-gift-popup-size-wrap>
          <button
            type="button"
            class="gift-popup__select"
            data-gift-popup-size-trigger
            role="combobox"
            aria-haspopup="listbox"
            aria-controls="gift-popup-size-listbox"
            aria-expanded="false"
            aria-labelledby="gift-popup-size-label"
          >
            <span class="gift-popup__select-value" data-gift-popup-size-value>Choose your size</span>
          </button>
          <span class="gift-popup__chevron" aria-hidden="true">
            {{- 'arrow-down.svg' | inline_asset_content -}}
          </span>
          <ul
            class="gift-popup__size-list"
            id="gift-popup-size-listbox"
            data-gift-popup-size-list
            role="listbox"
            aria-labelledby="gift-popup-size-label"
            hidden
          ></ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="gift-popup__notice" data-gift-popup-notice role="status" aria-live="polite" hidden></p>

    {% render 'gift-button',
      label: 'Add to cart',
      variant: 'invert',
      type: 'button',
      class: 'gift-popup__add',
      attributes: 'data-gift-popup-add'
    %}
  </div>
</div>
